# Supabase (auth + project persistence).
# Create a project at https://supabase.com/ then add URL and anon key.
# Enable Google and Email in Authentication → Providers for "Save Work" (Google + email/password).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key_here

# RentCast API key for real property values and comparable sales.
# Get a key at https://rentcast.io/ (free tier available).
# Leave unset to use demo/estimated data.
# VITE_RENTCAST_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Google Maps API key for address autocomplete (Places API).
# If autocomplete doesn't show or the input locks, open DevTools (F12) → Console and look for [Google Places] warnings.
#
# Key setup checklist (Google Cloud Console https://console.cloud.google.com/):
# 1. APIs & Services → Library → enable "Places API" and "Maps JavaScript API"
# 2. APIs & Services → Credentials → your API key → Application restrictions:
#    - Choose "HTTP referrers" and add:
#      http://localhost:* and https://localhost:* (dev)
#      https://expandeasenow.com/* and https://www.expandeasenow.com/* (production)
#    - Or use "None" for testing (less secure)
# 3. Billing: link a billing account (Google gives $200/month free credit; required for Maps/Places)
#
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Stripe (optional for soft launch). Use test keys until you enable payments.
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...

# --- Dream Home chat (backend server) ---
# Run the chat server: cd server && npm install && npm run dev
# Then set OPENAI_API_KEY in server/.env (create from server/.env.example).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# Optional: use a different model (default gpt-4o-mini).
# CHAT_MODEL=gpt-4o
# Optional: server port (default 3001).
# PORT=3001

# Frontend: optional override for chat API base URL (default /api, proxied to backend).
# VITE_CHAT_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api
